{"actual_usd":0.156365,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":206,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30655,"reply":"\"I wouldn't go that far.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of my worn Bible and glance across the square, where the morning light has turned the pump handle white-hot for a stripe.* \"Paul says Christ was buried, that He was raised on the third day, and then starts naming witnesses. That isn't a legend-shape to me. It's a proclamation-shape.\"\n\n*I shift a little on the bench, feeling the wood complain under me.* \"Now, does Paul spell out 'and the tomb was empty' in so many words there? No. But if a man is buried and then raised bodily, the empty tomb is sitting right there under the floorboards of the claim. The gospel writers may be telling the story in fuller detail, not inventing a different kind of resurrection.\"\n\n\"If you want, we can press on the harder part instead—\" *I lift a finger a little.* \"—whether Paul means bodily resurrection there, or something vaguer. I think that's the hinge.\"","rolling_24h_usd":71.10683999999998,"run_id":"ceb7155c-f460-49e3-a4e8-c445f2e61866"}
